{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "b1f7a2c0-1a2b-4c3d-9e10-n1rmaa0stage1",
    "name": "Nirmaan API",
    "description": "Nirmaan backend API collection. Auto-generated and kept in sync with the NestJS backend (apps/backend).\n\n## Import\nImport this file in Postman (Import > File), then ALSO import `Nirmaan.dev.postman_environment.json` and select the \"Nirmaan - Local Dev\" environment. Collection variables provide fallback defaults, but the test scripts write tokens to the ENVIRONMENT, so it must be selected.\n\n## Auto-saved variables\nTokens are captured automatically by request test scripts into the active ENVIRONMENT, so you almost never copy/paste:\n- `Auth / Verify OTP` and `Auth / Google Login` save `accessToken`, `refreshToken`, `userId`.\n- `Auth / Refresh Access Token` updates `accessToken`.\n- `Auth / Logout` clears `accessToken` + `refreshToken`.\n\nEvery protected request uses collection-level Bearer auth `{{accessToken}}`, so once you verify an OTP, the rest just work.\n\n## Typical flow\n1. `Auth / Request OTP` (read the 6-digit code from the backend server log).\n2. Set `otpCode` (environment variable) to that code.\n3. `Auth / Verify OTP` -> tokens saved automatically.\n4. `Users / Update Me (Onboarding)` -> sets name + pincode, flips profileComplete.\n5. `Users / Get Me`, `Areas / *`, etc.\n\nVersion: Stage 1 (Auth, Users, Areas).",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{accessToken}}", "type": "string" }]
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Auth",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Request OTP",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const res = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('returns expiresInSec', () => pm.expect(res).to.have.property('expiresInSec'));",
                  "console.log('OTP requested for', pm.environment.get('otpEmail'), '- read the 6-digit code from the backend server log, then set the otpCode variable.');"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{otpEmail}}\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/otp/request",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "otp", "request"]
            },
            "description": "POST /auth/otp/request -> { success, expiresInSec }. Rate limit: 3/hour per email. The code is logged by the dev server (email delivery not wired yet)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Verify OTP",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const res = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (res.accessToken) {",
                  "  pm.environment.set('accessToken', res.accessToken);",
                  "  pm.environment.set('refreshToken', res.refreshToken);",
                  "  console.log('Saved accessToken + refreshToken.');",
                  "}",
                  "if (res.user && res.user.id) pm.environment.set('userId', res.user.id);",
                  "pm.test('returns a JWT', () => pm.expect(res).to.have.property('accessToken'));",
                  "console.log('isNewUser:', res.isNewUser, '| profileComplete:', res.user && res.user.profileComplete);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{otpEmail}}\",\n  \"code\": \"{{otpCode}}\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/otp/verify",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "otp", "verify"]
            },
            "description": "POST /auth/otp/verify -> { accessToken, refreshToken, user, isNewUser }. Set otpCode to the code from the server log first."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Google Login",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const res = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200 && res.accessToken) {",
                  "  pm.environment.set('accessToken', res.accessToken);",
                  "  pm.environment.set('refreshToken', res.refreshToken);",
                  "  if (res.user && res.user.id) pm.environment.set('userId', res.user.id);",
                  "  console.log('Saved tokens from Google login. isNewUser:', res.isNewUser);",
                  "} else {",
                  "  console.log('Google login response:', res.error || res.message || pm.response.code);",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"idToken\": \"{{googleIdToken}}\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/google",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "google"]
            },
            "description": "POST /auth/google -> same shape as OTP verify. Returns 500 GOOGLE_NOT_CONFIGURED until GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID is set in the backend .env. Put a real Google ID token in the googleIdToken variable."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Refresh Access Token",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const res = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (res.accessToken) {",
                  "  pm.environment.set('accessToken', res.accessToken);",
                  "  console.log('Refreshed accessToken.');",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"refreshToken\": \"{{refreshToken}}\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "refresh"]
            },
            "description": "POST /auth/refresh -> { accessToken }. Uses the saved refreshToken."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Logout",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.environment.set('accessToken', '');",
                  "pm.environment.set('refreshToken', '');",
                  "console.log('Cleared accessToken + refreshToken.');"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/logout",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "logout"]
            },
            "description": "POST /auth/logout -> { success }. Requires Bearer token (inherited). Revokes the stored refresh token."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Users",
      "item": [
